Subject: Register generated Argo skin

Add the generated NadicodeAI-driven argo skin as a built-in skin while
keeping the volatile token colors and banner art in overlay. The patch
only wires structure into skin_engine.py and extends the existing skin
tests so dist/argo proves the generated skin loads and does not inherit
Hermes caduceus/kawaii/war glyphs.

Index: .sync-workdir/hermes_cli/skin_engine.py
===================================================================
--- .sync-workdir.orig/hermes_cli/skin_engine.py
+++ .sync-workdir/hermes_cli/skin_engine.py
@@ -161,7 +161,15 @@
 # Built-in skin definitions
 # =============================================================================
 
+try:
+    from hermes_cli._argo_skin import ARGO_SKIN_DATA as _ARGO_SKIN_DATA
+except Exception:  # pragma: no cover - keeps upstream imports usable without overlay
+    _ARGO_SKIN_DATA = {
+        "name": "argo",
+        "description": "NadicodeAI ink - generated skin data unavailable",
+    }
 _BUILTIN_SKINS: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]] = {
+    "argo": _ARGO_SKIN_DATA,
     "default": {
         "name": "default",
         "description": "Classic Hermes — gold and kawaii",
